Milford first appeared as a [[census-designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Milford had a population of 147. The population density was {{convert|27.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Milford was 120 (81.6%) [[White Americans|White]], 1 (0.7%) [[African Americans|African American]], 4 (2.7%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 4 (2.7%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 6 (4.1%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 12 (8.2%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 3 persons (2.0%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Milford CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0647472 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 29, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 66 households, out of which 16 (24.2%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 41 (62.1%) were married-couple households, 4 (6.1%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 11 (16.7%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 10 (15.2%) had a male householder with no partner present. 15 households (22.7%) were one person, and 4 (6.1%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.23.<ref name=DP1/> There were 48 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (72.7% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Milford CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0647472 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 29, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 25 people (17.0%) under the age of 18, 5 people (3.4%) aged 18 to 24, 20 people (13.6%) aged 25 to 44, 56 people (38.1%) aged 45 to 64, and 41 people (27.9%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 53.5{{nbsp}}years. There were 74 males and 73 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 71 housing units at an average density of {{convert|13.4|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 66 (93.0%) were occupied. Of these, 57 (86.4%) were owner-occupied, and 9 (13.6%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

